name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Summary of Significant Accounting Policies Nature of Operations Google was incorporated in California in September 1998 and re-incorporated in the State of Delaware in August 2003.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: In 2015, we implemented a holding company reorganization, and as a result, Alphabet Inc. ("Alphabet") became the successor issuer to Google.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We generate revenues by delivering relevant, cost-effective online advertising; cloud-based solutions that provide enterprise customers with infrastructure and platform services as well as communication and collaboration tools; sales of other products and services, such as fees received for consumer subscription-based products, apps and in-app purchases, and devices.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Basis of Consolidation The consolidated financial statements of Alphabet include the accounts of Alphabet and entities consolidated under the variable interest and voting models. Intercompany balances and transactions have been eliminated.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Use of Estimates Preparation of consolidated financial statements in conformity with GAAP requires us to make estimates and assumptions that affect the amounts reported and disclosed in the financial statements and the accompanying notes.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Actual results could differ materially from these estimates due to uncertainties.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: On an ongoing basis, we evaluate our estimates, including those related to the allowance for credit losses; content licenses; contingent liabilities; fair values of financial instruments and goodwill; income taxes; inventory; and useful lives of property and equipment, among others.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We base our estimates on assumptions, both historical and forward looking, that are believed to be reasonable, and the results of which form the basis for making judgments about the carrying values of assets and liabilities.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: In January 2023, we completed an assessment of the useful lives of our servers and network equipment and adjusted the estimated useful life of our servers from four years to six years and the estimated useful life of certain network equipment from five years to six years.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: This change in accounting estimate was effective beginning in fiscal year 2023.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Based on the carrying value of servers and certain network equipment as of December 31, 2022, and those placed in service during the year ended December 31, 2023, the effect of this change in estimate was a reduction in depreciation expense of $3.9 billion and an increase in net income of $3.0 billion, or $0.24 per basic and $0.24 per diluted share, for the year ended December 31, 2023.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Revenue Recognition Revenues are recognized when control of the promised goods or services is transferred to our customers, and the collectibility of an amount that we expect in exchange for those goods or services is probable.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Sales and other similar taxes are excluded from revenues.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Advertising Revenues We generate advertising revenues primarily by delivering advertising on:

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Google Search and other properties, including revenues from traffic generated by search distribution partners who use Google.com as their default search in browsers, toolbars, etc. and other Google owned and operated properties like Gmail, Google Maps, and Google Play;

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: YouTube properties; and Google Network properties, including revenues from Google Network properties participating in AdMob, AdSense, and Google Ad Manager.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our customers generally purchase advertising inventory through Google Ads, Google Ad Manager, Google Display & Video 360, and Google Marketing Platform, among others.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We offer advertising by delivering both performance and brand advertising.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We recognize revenues for performance advertising when a user engages with the advertisement.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: For brand advertising, we recognize revenues when the ad is displayed, or a user views the ad.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: For ads placed on Google Network properties, we evaluate whether we are the principal (i.e., report revenues on a gross basis) or agent (i.e., report revenues on a net basis).

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Generally, we report advertising revenues for ads placed on Google Network properties on a gross basis, that is, the amounts billed to our customers are recorded as revenues,

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Alphabet Inc.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: and amounts paid to Google Network partners are recorded as cost of revenues.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Where we are the principal, we control the advertising inventory before it is transferred to our customers.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our control is evidenced by our sole ability to monetize the advertising inventory before it is transferred to our customers and is further supported by us being primarily responsible to our customers and having a level of discretion in establishing pricing.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Google Subscriptions, Platforms, and Devices Google subscriptions, platforms, and devices revenues consist of revenues from:

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: consumer subscriptions, which primarily include revenues from YouTube services, such YouTube TV, YouTube Music and Premium, and NFL Sunday Ticket, as well as Google One;

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: platforms, which primarily include revenues from Google Play from the sales of apps and in-app purchases;

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: devices, which primarily include sales of the Pixel family of devices; and

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: other products and services.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Subscription revenues are recognized ratably over the period of the subscription, primarily monthly.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We report revenues from Google Play app sales and in-app purchases on a net basis, because our performance obligation is to facilitate a transaction between app developers and end users, for which we earn a service fee.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Google Cloud Revenues Google Cloud revenues consist of revenues from: Google Cloud Platform, which generates consumption-based fees and subscriptions for infrastructure, platform, and other services.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: These services provide access to solutions such as cybersecurity, databases, analytics, and AI offerings including our AI infrastructure, Vertex AI platform, and Duet AI for Google Cloud;

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Google Workspace, which includes subscriptions for cloud-based communication and collaboration tools for enterprises, such as Calendar, Gmail, Docs, Drive, and Meet, with integrated features like Duet AI in Google Workspace; and

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: other enterprise services.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our cloud services are generally provided on either a consumption or subscription basis and may have contract terms longer than a year.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Revenues related to cloud services provided on a consumption basis are recognized when the customer utilizes the services, based on the quantity of services consumed.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Revenues related to cloud services provided on a subscription basis are recognized ratably over the contract term as the customer receives and consumes the benefits of the cloud services.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Arrangements with Multiple Performance Obligations Our contracts with customers may include multiple performance obligations.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: For such arrangements, we allocate revenues to each performance obligation based on its relative standalone selling price.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We generally determine standalone selling prices based on the prices charged to customers.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Customer Incentives and Credits Certain customers receive cash-based incentives or credits, which are accounted for as variable consideration.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We estimate these amounts based on the expected amount to be provided to customers and reduce revenues.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We believe that there will not be significant changes to our estimates of variable consideration.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Sales Commissions We expense sales commissions when incurred when the period of the expected benefit is one year or less.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We recognize an asset for certain sales commissions and amortize if the expected benefit period is greater than one year.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: These costs are recorded within sales and marketing expenses.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Cost of Revenues Cost of revenues consists of TAC and other costs of revenues.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: TAC includes: amounts paid to our distribution partners who make available our search access points and services. Our distribution partners include browser providers, mobile carriers, original equipment manufacturers, and software developers; and

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: amounts paid to Google Network partners primarily for ads displayed on their properties.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Alphabet Inc.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Other cost of revenues includes: compensation expense related to our data centers and other operations such as content review and customer and product support;

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: content acquisition costs, which are payments to content providers from whom we license video and other content for distribution on YouTube and Google Play (we pay fees to these content providers based on revenues generated or a flat fee);

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: depreciation expense related to our technical infrastructure; and inventory and other costs related to the devices we sell.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Software Development Costs We expense software development costs, including costs to develop software products or the software component of products to be sold, leased, or marketed to external users, before technological feasibility is reached.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Technological feasibility is typically reached shortly before the release of such products.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: As a result, development costs that meet the criteria for capitalization were not material for the periods presented.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Software development costs also include costs to develop software to be used solely to meet internal needs and cloud-based applications used to deliver our services.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We capitalize development costs related to these software applications once the preliminary project stage is complete and it is probable that the project will be completed and the software will be used to perform the function intended.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Costs capitalized for developing such software applications were not material for the periods presented.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Stock-based Compensation Stock-based compensation (SBC) primarily consists of Alphabet restricted stock units (RSUs).

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: RSUs are equity classified and measured at the fair market value of the underlying stock at the grant date.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We recognize RSU expense using the straight-line attribution method over the requisite service period and account for forfeitures as they occur.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: For RSUs, shares are issued on the vesting dates net of the applicable statutory income tax withholding to be paid by us on behalf of our employees.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: As a result, fewer shares are issued than the number of RSUs outstanding, and the income tax withholding is recorded as a reduction to additional paid-in capital.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Additionally, SBC includes other stock-based awards, such as performance stock units (PSUs) that include market conditions and awards that may be settled in cash or the stock of certain Other Bet companies.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: PSUs and certain awards granted by Other Bet companies are equity classified and expense is recognized over the requisite service period.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Certain awards granted by Other Bet companies are liability classified and remeasured at fair value through settlement.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The fair value of awards granted by Other Bet companies is based on the equity valuation of the respective Other Bet company.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Advertising and Promotional Expenses We expense advertising and promotional costs in the period in which they are incurred.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: For the years ended December 31, 2021, 2022, and 2023, advertising and promotional expenses totaled approximately $7.9 billion, $9.2 billion, and $8.7 billion, respectively.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Performance Fees Performance fees refer to compensation arrangements with payouts based on realized returns from certain investments.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We record compensation expense based on the estimated payouts on an ongoing basis, which may result in expense recognized before investment returns are realized and compensation is paid and may require the use of unobservable inputs.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Performance fees are recorded as a component of OI&E.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Fair Value Measurements Fair value is an exit price, representing the amount that would be received to sell an asset or paid to transfer a liability in an orderly transaction between market participants.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: As such, fair value is a market-based measurement that is determined based on assumptions that market participants would use in pricing an asset or a liability.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Assets and liabilities recorded at fair value are measured and classified in accordance with a three-tier fair value hierarchy based on the observability of the inputs available in the market used to measure fair value:

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Level 1 - Observable inputs that reflect quoted prices (unadjusted) for identical assets or liabilities in active markets.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Alphabet Inc.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Level 2 - Inputs that are based upon quoted prices for similar instruments in active markets, quoted prices for identical or similar instruments in markets that are not active, and model-based valuation techniques for which all significant inputs are observable in the market or can be derived from observable market data.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Where applicable, these models project future cash flows and discount the future amounts to a present value using market-based observable inputs including interest rate curves, foreign exchange rates, and credit ratings.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Level 3 - Unobservable inputs that are supported by little or no market activities.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The fair value hierarchy requires an entity to maximize the use of observable inputs and minimize the use of unobservable inputs when measuring fair value.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The determination of fair value involves the use of appropriate valuation methods and relevant inputs into valuation models.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our financial assets and liabilities that are measured at fair value on a recurring basis include cash equivalents, marketable securities, derivative financial instruments, and certain non-marketable debt securities.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our financial assets measured at fair value on a nonrecurring basis include non-marketable equity securities.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Other financial assets and liabilities are carried at cost with fair value disclosed, if required.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We measure certain other instruments, including SBC awards settled in the stock of Other Bet companies, and certain assets and liabilities acquired in a business combination, also at fair value on a nonrecurring basis.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Financial Instruments Our financial instruments include cash, cash equivalents, marketable and non-marketable securities, derivative financial instruments and accounts receivable.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Credit Risks We are subject to credit risk primarily from cash equivalents, marketable debt securities, derivative financial instruments, including foreign exchange contracts, and accounts receivable.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We manage our credit risk exposure through timely assessment of our counterparty creditworthiness, credit limits and use of collateral management.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Foreign exchange contracts are transacted with various financial institutions with high credit standing.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Accounts receivable are typically unsecured and are derived from revenues earned from customers located around the world.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We manage our credit risk exposure by performing ongoing evaluations to determine customer credit and we limit the amount of credit we extend.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We generally do not require collateral from our customers.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Cash Equivalents We invest excess cash primarily in government bonds, corporate debt securities, mortgage-backed and asset-backed securities, time deposits, and money market funds.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Marketable Securities We classify all marketable debt securities that have effective maturities of three months or less from the date of purchase as cash equivalents and those with effective maturities of greater than three months as marketable securities on our Consolidated Balance Sheets.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We determine the appropriate classification of our investments in marketable debt securities at the time of purchase and reevaluate such designation at each balance sheet date.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We have classified and accounted for our marketable debt securities as available-for-sale.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: After consideration of our risk versus reward objectives, as well as our liquidity requirements, we may sell these debt securities prior to their effective maturities.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: As we view these securities as available to support current operations, we classify highly liquid securities with maturities beyond 12 months as current assets under the caption marketable securities on the Consolidated Balance Sheets.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We carry these securities at fair value, and report the unrealized gains and losses, net of taxes, as a component of stockholders' equity, except for the changes in allowance for expected credit losses, which are recorded in OI&E.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: For certain marketable debt securities we have elected the fair value option, for which changes in fair value are recorded in OI&E.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We determine any realized gains or losses on the sale of marketable debt securities on a specific identification method, and we record such gains and losses as a component of OI&E.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our investments in marketable equity securities are measured at fair value with the related gains and losses, including unrealized, recognized in OI&E.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We classify our marketable equity securities subject to long-term lock-up restrictions beyond 12 months as other non-current assets on the Consolidated Balance Sheets.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Non-Marketable Securities Non-marketable securities primarily consist of equity securities.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We account for non-marketable equity securities through which we exercise significant influence but do not have control over the investee under the equity method.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: All other non-marketable equity securities that we hold are primarily accounted for under the measurement alternative.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Under the measurement alternative, the carrying value is measured at cost, less any impairment, plus or minus

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Alphabet Inc.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: changes resulting from observable price changes in orderly transactions for identical or similar investments of the same issuer.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Adjustments are determined primarily based on a market approach as of the transaction date and are recorded as a component of OI&E.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Non-marketable securities that do not have effective contractual maturity dates are classified as other non-current assets on the Consolidated Balance Sheets.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Derivative Financial Instruments See Note 3 for the accounting policy pertaining to derivative financial instruments.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Accounts Receivable Our payment terms for accounts receivable vary by the types and locations of our customers and the products or services offered.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The term between invoicing and when payment is due is not significant.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: For certain products or services and customers, we require payment before the products or services are delivered to the customer.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Additionally, accounts receivable includes amounts for services performed in advance of the right to invoice the customer.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We maintain an allowance for credit losses for accounts receivable, which is recorded as an offset to accounts receivable, and changes in such are classified as general and administrative expense in the Consolidated Statements of Income.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We assess collectibility by reviewing accounts receivable on a collective basis where similar characteristics exist and on an individual basis when we identify specific customers with known disputes or collectibility issues.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: In determining the amount of the allowance for credit losses, we consider historical collectibility based on past due status and make judgments about the creditworthiness of customers based on ongoing credit evaluations.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We also consider customer-specific information, current market conditions, and reasonable and supportable forecasts of future economic conditions.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Other Our financial instruments also include debt and equity investments in companies with which we also entered into commercial arrangements at or near the same time.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: For these transactions, judgment is required in assessing the substance of the arrangements, including assessing whether the components of the arrangements should be accounted for as separate transactions under the applicable GAAP, and determining the value of the components of the arrangements, including the fair value of the investments.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Additionally, if our investment in such companies becomes impaired, any remaining performance obligations would be reassessed and may be reduced.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Impairment of Investments We periodically review our debt and non-marketable equity securities for impairment.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: For debt securities in an unrealized loss position, we determine whether a credit loss exists.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The credit loss is estimated by considering available information relevant to the collectibility of the security and information about past events, current conditions, and reasonable and supportable forecasts.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Any credit loss is recorded as a charge to OI&E, not to exceed the amount of the unrealized loss.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Unrealized losses other than the credit loss are recognized in AOCI.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: If we have an intent to sell, or if it is more likely than not that we will be required to sell a debt security in an unrealized loss position before recovery of its amortized cost basis, we will write down the security to its fair value and record the corresponding charge as a component of OI&E.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: For non-marketable equity securities, including equity method investments, we consider whether impairment indicators exist by evaluating the companies' financial and liquidity position and access to capital resources, among other indicators.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: If the assessment indicates that the investment is impaired, we write down the investment to its fair value by recording the corresponding charge as a component of OI&E.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We prepare quantitative measurements of the fair value of our equity investments using a market approach or an income approach.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Inventory Inventory consists primarily of finished goods and is stated at the lower of cost and net realizable value. Cost is computed using the first-in, first-out method.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Variable Interest Entities We determine at the inception of each arrangement whether an entity in which we have made an investment or in which we have other variable interests is considered a variable interest entity (VIE).

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We consolidate VIEs when we are the primary beneficiary.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We are the primary beneficiary of a VIE when we have the power to direct activities that most significantly affect the economic performance of the VIE and have the obligation to absorb the majority of their losses

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Alphabet Inc.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: or benefits. If we are not the primary beneficiary in a VIE, we account for the investment or other variable interests in a VIE in accordance with applicable GAAP.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Periodically, we assess whether any changes in our interest or relationship with the entity affect our determination of whether the entity is a VIE and, if so, whether we are the primary beneficiary.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Property and Equipment Property and equipment includes the following categories: land and buildings, information technology assets, construction in progress, leasehold improvements, and furniture and fixtures.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Land and buildings include land, offices, data centers, and related building improvements.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Information technology assets include servers and network equipment.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Construction in progress is the construction or development of property and equipment that have not yet been placed in service.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Property and equipment are stated at cost less accumulated depreciation.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Depreciation is recorded using the straight-line method over the estimated useful lives of the assets, which we regularly evaluate.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Land is not depreciated.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We depreciate buildings over periods of seven to 25 years.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We depreciate information technology assets generally over a period of six years for servers and network equipment.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We depreciate leasehold improvements over the shorter of the remaining lease term or the estimated useful lives of the assets.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Depreciation for buildings, information technology assets, leasehold improvements, and furniture and fixtures commences once they are ready for our intended use.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Goodwill We allocate goodwill to reporting units based on the expected benefit from the business combination.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We evaluate our reporting units periodically, as well as when changes in our operating segments occur.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: For changes in reporting units, we reassign goodwill using a relative fair value allocation approach.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We test our goodwill for impairment at least annually, or more frequently if events or changes in circumstances indicate that the asset may be impaired.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Goodwill impairments were not material for the periods presented.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Leases We determine if an arrangement is a lease at inception.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our lease agreements generally contain lease and non-lease components.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Payments under our lease arrangements are primarily fixed.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Non-lease components primarily include payments for maintenance and utilities.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We combine fixed payments for non-lease components with lease payments and account for them together as a single lease component which increases the amount of our lease assets and liabilities.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Certain lease agreements contain variable payments, which are expensed as incurred and not included in the lease assets and liabilities. These amounts primarily include payments affected by the Consumer Price Index, and payments for maintenance and utilities.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Lease assets and liabilities are recognized at the present value of the future lease payments at the lease commencement date.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The interest rate used to determine the present value of the future lease payments is our incremental borrowing rate, because the interest rate implicit in our leases is not readily determinable.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our incremental borrowing rate is estimated to approximate the interest rate on a collateralized basis with similar terms and payments, and in economic environments where the leased asset is located.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our lease terms include periods under options to extend or terminate the lease when it is reasonably certain that we will exercise that option.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We generally use the base, non-cancelable, lease term when determining the lease assets and liabilities.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Lease assets also include any prepaid lease payments and lease incentives.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Operating lease assets and liabilities are included on our Consolidated Balance Sheets.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The current portion of our operating lease liabilities is included in accrued expenses and other current liabilities, and the long-term portion is included in operating lease liabilities.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Finance lease assets are included in property and equipment, net.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Finance lease liabilities are included in accrued expenses and other current liabilities or long-term debt.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Operating lease expense (excluding variable lease costs) is recognized on a straight-line basis over the lease term.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Impairment of Long-Lived Assets We review leases, property and equipment, and intangible assets, excluding goodwill, for impairment when events or changes in circumstances indicate the carrying amount may not be recoverable.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The evaluation is performed at the lowest level of identifiable cash flows independent of other assets.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We measure recoverability of these assets by comparing the carrying amounts to the future undiscounted cash flows that the assets or the asset group are expected

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Alphabet Inc.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: to generate. If the carrying value of the assets or asset group is not recoverable, the impairment recognized is measured as the amount by which the carrying value exceeds its fair value.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Income Taxes We account for income taxes using the asset and liability method, under which we recognize the amount of taxes payable or refundable for the current year and deferred tax assets and liabilities for the future tax consequences of events that have been recognized in our financial statements or tax returns.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We measure current and deferred tax assets and liabilities based on provisions of enacted tax law.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We evaluate the likelihood of future realization of our deferred tax assets based on all available evidence and establish a valuation allowance to reduce deferred tax assets when it is more likely than not that they will not be realized or release a valuation allowance to increase deferred tax assets when it is more likely than not that they will be realized.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We have elected to account for the tax effects of the global intangible low tax Income provision as a current period expense.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We recognize the financial statement effects of a tax position when it is more likely than not that, based on technical merits, the position will be sustained upon examination.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The tax benefits of the position recognized in the financial statements are then measured based on the largest amount of benefit that is greater than 50% likely to be realized upon settlement with a taxing authority.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: In addition, we recognize interest and penalties related to unrecognized tax benefits as a component of the income tax provision.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Business Combinations We include the results of operations of the businesses that we acquire as of the acquisition date.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We allocate the purchase price of the acquisitions to the assets acquired and liabilities assumed based on their estimated fair values, except for revenue contracts acquired, which are recognized in accordance with our revenue recognition policy.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The excess of the purchase price over the fair values of identifiable assets and liabilities is recorded as goodwill.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Acquisition-related expenses are recognized separately from the business combination and are expensed as incurred.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Foreign Currency We translate the financial statements of our international subsidiaries to U.S. dollars using month-end exchange rates for assets and liabilities, and average rates for the annual period derived from month-end exchange rates for revenues, costs, and expenses.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We record translation gains and losses in AOCI as a component of stockholders' equity.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We reflect net foreign exchange transaction gains and losses resulting from the conversion of the transaction currency to functional currency as a component of foreign currency exchange gain (loss) in OI&E.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Recent Accounting Pronouncements In November 2023, the Financial Standards Accounting Board (FASB) issued Accounting Standards Update (ASU) 2023-07 "Segment Reporting (Topic 280):Improvements to Reportable Segment Disclosures" which expands annual and interim disclosure requirements for reportable segments, primarily through enhanced disclosures about significant segment expenses.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: ASU 2023-07 is effective for our annual periods beginning January 1, 2024, and for interim periods beginning January 1, 2025, with early adoption permitted.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We are currently evaluating the potential effect that the updated standard will have on our financial statement disclosures.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: In December 2023, the FASB issued ASU 2023-09 "Income Taxes (Topics 740): Improvements to Income Tax Disclosures" to expand the disclosure requirements for income taxes, specifically related to the rate reconciliation and income taxes paid.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: ASU 2023-09 is effective for our annual periods beginning January 1, 2025, with early adoption permitted.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We are currently evaluating the potential effect that the updated standard will have on our financial statement disclosures.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We expect to recognize approximately half of the revenue backlog as revenues over the next 24 months with the remaining to be recognized thereafter.

sentence: Debt securities are measured at fair value and classified within Level 2 in the fair value hierarchy, because we use quoted market prices to the extent available or alternative pricing sources and models utilizing market observable inputs to determine fair value.

sentence: Our non-marketable equity securities are investments in privately held companies without readily determinable market values.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Non-marketable equity securities that have been remeasured during the period based on observable transactions are classified within Level 2 or Level 3 in the fair value hierarchy because we estimate the value based on valuation methods, including option pricing models, market comparable approach, and common stock equivalent method, which may include a combination of the observable transaction price at the transaction date and other unobservable inputs including volatility, expected time to exit, risk free rate, and the rights, and obligations of the securities we hold.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: These inputs significantly vary based on investment type.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The fair value of non-marketable equity securities that have been remeasured due to impairment are classified within Level 3.

sentence: Derivative Financial Instruments We use derivative instruments to manage risks relating to our ongoing business operations.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The primary risk managed is foreign exchange risk.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We use foreign currency contracts to reduce the risk that our cash flows, earnings, and investment in foreign subsidiaries will be adversely affected by foreign currency exchange rate fluctuations.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We also enter into derivative instruments to partially offset our exposure to other risks and enhance investment returns.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We recognize derivative instruments in the Consolidated Balance Sheets at fair value and classify the derivatives primarily within Level 2 in the fair value hierarchy.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We present our collar contracts (an option strategy comprised of a combination of purchased and written options) at net fair values and present all other derivatives at gross fair values.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The accounting treatment for derivatives is based on the intended use and hedge designation.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Cash Flow Hedges We designate foreign currency forward and option contracts (including collars) as cash flow hedges to hedge certain forecasted revenue transactions denominated in currencies other than the U.S. dollar.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: These contracts have maturities of 24 months or less.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Cash flow hedge amounts included in the assessment of hedge effectiveness are deferred in AOCI and subsequently reclassified to revenue when the hedged item is recognized in earnings.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We exclude forward points and time value from our assessment of hedge effectiveness and amortize them on a straight-line basis over the life of the hedging instrument in revenues.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The difference between fair value changes of the excluded component and the amount amortized to revenues is recorded in AOCI.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: As of December 31, 2023, the net accumulated gain on our foreign currency cash flow hedges before tax effect was $47 million, which is expected to be reclassified from AOCI into revenues within the next 12 months.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Fair Value Hedges We designate foreign currency forward contracts as fair value hedges to hedge foreign currency risks for our marketable securities denominated in currencies other than the U.S. dollar.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Fair value hedge amounts included in the assessment of hedge effectiveness are recognized in OI&E, along with the offsetting gains and losses of the related hedged items.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We exclude forward points from the assessment of hedge effectiveness and recognize changes in the excluded component in OI&E.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Net Investment Hedges We designate foreign currency forward contracts as net investment hedges to hedge the foreign currency risks related to our investment in foreign subsidiaries.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Net investment hedge amounts included in the assessment of hedge effectiveness are recognized in AOCI along with the foreign currency translation adjustment.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We exclude forward points from the assessment of hedge effectiveness and recognize changes in the excluded component in OI&E.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Other Derivatives We enter into foreign currency forward and option contracts that are not designated as hedging instruments to hedge intercompany transactions and other monetary assets or liabilities denominated in currencies other than the functional currency of a subsidiary.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Gains and losses on these derivatives that are not designated as accounting hedges are primarily recorded in OI&E along with the foreign currency gains and losses on monetary assets and liabilities.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We also use derivatives not designated as hedging instruments to manage risks relating to interest rates, commodity prices, credit exposures, and to enhance investment returns.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: From time to time, we enter into derivatives to hedge the market price risk on certain of our marketable equity securities.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Gains and losses arising from other derivatives are primarily reflected within the "other" component of OI&E.

sentence: These VIEs include private companies that are primarily early stage companies and certain renewable energy entities in which activities involve power generation using renewable sources.

sentence: We have determined that the governance structures of these entities do not allow us to direct the activities that would significantly affect their economic performance.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Therefore, we are not the primary beneficiary, and the results of operations and financial position of these VIEs are not included in our consolidated financial statements.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We account for these investments primarily as non-marketable equity securities or equity method investments.

sentence: The maximum exposure of these unconsolidated VIEs is generally based on the current carrying value of the investments and any future funding commitments.

sentence: Legal Matters We record a liability when we believe that it is probable that a loss has been incurred, and the amount can be reasonably estimated.

sentence: Antitrust Investigations On November 30, 2010, the EC's Directorate General for Competition opened an investigation into various antitrust-related complaints against us.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: On June 27, 2017, the EC announced its decision that certain actions taken by Google regarding its display and ranking of shopping search results and ads infringed European competition law.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The EC decision imposed a 2.4 billion ($2.7 billion as of June 27, 2017) fine.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: On September 11, 2017, we appealed the EC decision to the General Court, and on September 27, 2017, we implemented product changes to bring shopping ads into compliance with the EC's decision.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We recognized a charge of $2.7 billion for the fine in the second quarter of 2017.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: On November 10, 2021, the General Court rejected our appeal, and we subsequently filed an appeal with the European Court of Justice on January 20, 2022.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: On July 18, 2018, the EC announced its decision that certain provisions in Google's Android-related distribution agreements infringed European competition law.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The EC decision imposed a 4.3 billion ($5.1 billion as of June 30, 2018) fine and directed the termination of the conduct at issue.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: On October 9, 2018, we appealed the EC decision, and on October 29, 2018, we implemented changes to certain of our Android distribution practices.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: On September 14, 2022, the General Court reduced the fine from 4.3 billion to 4.1 billion.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We subsequently filed an appeal with the European Court of Justice.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: In 2018, we recognized a charge of $5.1 billion for the fine, which we reduced by $217 million in 2022.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: On March 20, 2019, the EC announced its decision that certain contractual provisions in agreements that Google had with AdSense for Search partners infringed European competition law.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The EC decision imposed a fine of 1.5 billion ($1.7 billion as of March 20, 2019) and directed actions related to AdSense for Search partners' agreements, which we implemented prior to the decision.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: On June 4, 2019, we appealed the EC decision.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We recognized a charge of $1.7 billion for the fine in the first quarter of 2019.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: From time to time we are subject to formal and informal inquiries and investigations on various competition matters by regulatory authorities in the U.S., Europe, and other jurisdictions globally.

sentence: In August 2019, we began receiving civil investigative demands from the U.S. Department of Justice (DOJ) requesting information and documents relating to our prior antitrust investigations and certain aspects of our business.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The DOJ and a number of state Attorneys General filed a lawsuit in the U.S. District Court for the District of Columbia on October 20, 2020 alleging that Google violated U.S. antitrust laws relating to Search and Search advertising.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The trial ended on November 16, 2023, and we expect a decision in 2024.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Further, in June 2022, the Australian Competition and Consumer Commission (ACCC) and the United Kingdom's Competition and Markets Authority (CMA) each opened an investigation into Search distribution practices.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: On December 16, 2020, a number of state Attorneys General filed an antitrust complaint in the U.S. District Court for the Eastern District of Texas, alleging that Google violated U.S. antitrust laws as well as state deceptive trade laws relating to its advertising technology, and a trial is scheduled for March 2025.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Additionally, on January 24, 2023, the DOJ, along with a number of state Attorneys General, filed an antitrust complaint in the U.S. District Court for the Eastern District of Virginia alleging that Google's digital advertising technology products violate U.S. antitrust laws, and on April 17, 2023, a number of additional state Attorneys General joined the complaint.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The EC, the CMA, and the ACCC each opened a formal investigation into Google's advertising technology business practices on June 22, 2021, May 25, 2022, and June 29, 2022, respectively.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: On June 14, 2023, the EC issued a Statement of Objections (SO) informing Google of its preliminary view that Google violated European antitrust laws relating to its advertising technology.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We responded to the SO on December 1, 2023.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: On July 7, 2021, a number of state Attorneys General filed an antitrust complaint in the U.S. District Court for the Northern District of California, alleging that Google's operation of Android and Google Play violated U.S. antitrust laws and state antitrust and consumer protection laws.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: In September 2023, we reached a settlement in principle with 50 state Attorneys General and three territories.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The U.S. District Court subsequently vacated the trial date with the states, and any final approval of the settlement is expected to occur in 2024.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: In May 2022, the EC and the CMA each opened investigations into Google Play's business practices.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Korean regulators are investigating Google Play's billing practices, including a formal review in May 2022 of Google's compliance with the new app store billing regulations.

sentence: We believe we have strong arguments against these claims and will defend ourselves vigorously. We continue to cooperate with federal and state regulators in the U.S., the EC, and other regulators around the world.

sentence: Privacy Matters We are subject to a number of privacy-related laws and regulations, and we currently are party to a number of privacy investigations and lawsuits ongoing in multiple jurisdictions.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: For example, there are ongoing investigations and litigation in the U.S. and the EU, including those relating to our collection and use of location information and advertising practices, which could result in significant fines, judgments, and product changes.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Patent and Intellectual Property Claims We have had patent, copyright, trade secret, and trademark infringement lawsuits filed against us claiming that certain of our products, services, and technologies infringe others' intellectual property rights.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Adverse results in these lawsuits may include awards of substantial monetary damages, costly royalty or licensing agreements, or orders preventing us from offering certain features, functionalities, products, or services.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: As a result, we may have to change our business practices and develop non-infringing products or technologies, which could result in a loss of revenues for us and otherwise harm our business.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: In addition, the U.S. International Trade Commission (ITC) has increasingly become an important forum to litigate intellectual property disputes because an ultimate loss in an ITC action can result in a prohibition on importing infringing products into the U.S. Because the U.S. is an important market, a prohibition on importation could have an adverse effect on us, including preventing us from importing many important products into the U.S. or necessitating workarounds that may limit certain features of our products.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Furthermore, many of our agreements with our customers and partners require us to indemnify them against certain intellectual property infringement claims, which would increase our costs as a result of defending such claims, and may require that we pay significant damages if there were an adverse ruling in any such claims.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: In addition, our customers and partners may discontinue the use of our products, services, and technologies, as a result of injunctions or otherwise, which could result in loss of revenues and adversely affect our business.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Other We are subject to claims, lawsuits, regulatory and government investigations, other proceedings, and consent orders involving competition, intellectual property, data security, tax and related compliance, labor and employment, commercial disputes, content generated by our users, goods and services offered by advertisers or publishers using our platforms, personal injury, consumer protection, and other matters.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: For example, in December 2023, a California jury delivered a verdict in Epic Games v. Google finding that Google violated antitrust laws related to Google Play's business.

sentence: The presiding judge will determine remedies in 2024, and the range of potential remedies vary widely.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We plan to appeal.

sentence: Note 11. Stockholders' Equity Class A and Class B Common Stock and Class C Capital Stock

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our Board of Directors has authorized three classes of stock, Class A and Class B common stock, and Class C capital stock.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The rights of the holders of each class of our common and capital stock are identical, except with respect to voting.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Each share of Class A common stock is entitled to one vote per share.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Each share of Class B common stock is entitled to 10 votes per share.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Class C capital stock has no voting rights, except as required by applicable law.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Shares of Class B common stock may be converted at any time at the option of the stockholder and automatically convert upon sale or transfer to Class A common stock.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Net Income Per Share We compute net income per share of Class A, Class B, and Class C stock using the two-class method.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Basic net income per share is computed using the weighted-average number of shares outstanding during the period.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Diluted net income per share is computed using the weighted-average number of shares and the effect of potentially dilutive securities outstanding during the period.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Potentially dilutive securities consist of RSUs and other contingently issuable shares.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The dilutive effect of outstanding RSUs and other contingently issuable shares is reflected in diluted earnings per share by application of the treasury stock method.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The computation of the diluted net income per share of Class A stock assumes the conversion of Class B stock, while the diluted net income per share of Class B stock does not assume the conversion of those shares.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The rights, including the liquidation and dividend rights, of the holders of our Class A, Class B, and Class C stock are identical, except with respect to voting.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Furthermore, there are a number of safeguards built into our certificate of incorporation, as well as Delaware law, which preclude our Board of Directors from declaring or paying unequal per share dividends on our Class A, Class B, and Class C stock.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Specifically, Delaware law provides that amendments to our certificate of incorporation which would have the effect of adversely altering the rights, powers, or preferences of a given class of stock must be approved by the class of stock adversely affected by the proposed amendment.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: In addition, our certificate of incorporation provides that before any such amendment may be put to a stockholder vote, it must be approved by the unanimous consent of our Board of Directors.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: As a result, the undistributed earnings for each year are allocated based on the contractual participation rights of the Class A, Class B, and Class C stock as if the earnings for the year had been distributed.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: As the liquidation and dividend rights are identical, the undistributed earnings are allocated on a proportionate basis.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: In the years ended December 31, 2021, 2022, and 2023, the net income per share amounts are the same for Class A, Class B, and Class C stock because the holders of each class are entitled to equal per share dividends or distributions in liquidation in accordance with the Amended and Restated Certificate of Incorporation of Alphabet Inc.

sentence: As of December 31, 2022 and 2023, we accrued $346 million and $622 million in interest and penalties in provision for income taxes, respectively.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We file income tax returns in the U.S. federal jurisdiction and in many state and foreign jurisdictions.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our two major tax jurisdictions are the U.S. federal and Ireland.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We are subject to the continuous examination of our income tax returns by the IRS and other tax authorities.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The IRS is currently examining our 2016 through 2021 tax returns.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We have also received tax assessments in multiple foreign jurisdictions asserting transfer pricing adjustments or permanent establishment.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We continue to defend such claims as presented.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The tax years 2016 through 2022 remain subject to examination by the appropriate governmental agencies for Irish tax purposes. There are other ongoing audits in various other jurisdictions that are not material to our financial statements.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We regularly assess the likelihood of adverse outcomes resulting from these examinations to determine the adequacy of our provision for income taxes.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We continue to monitor the progress of ongoing discussions with tax authorities and the effect, if any, of the expected expiration of the statute of limitations in various taxing jurisdictions.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We believe that an adequate provision has been made for any adjustments that may result from tax examinations.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: However, the outcome of tax audits cannot be predicted with certainty.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: If any issues addressed in our tax audits are resolved in a manner not consistent with management's expectations, we could be required to adjust our provision for income taxes in the period such resolutions occur.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Although the timing of resolution, settlement, and closure of audits is not certain, it is reasonably possible that our unrecognized tax benefits from certain U.S. federal, state, and non U.S. tax positions could decrease by approximately $700 million in the next 12 months.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Positions that may be resolved include various U.S. and non-U.S. matters.

sentence: Note 15. Information about Segments and Geographic Areas We report our segment results as Google Services, Google Cloud, and Other Bets:

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Google Services includes products and services such as ads, Android, Chrome, devices, Google Maps, Google Play, Search, and YouTube.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Google Services generates revenues primarily from advertising; fees received for consumer subscription-based products such as YouTube TV, YouTube Music and Premium, and NFL Sunday Ticket; the sale of apps and in-app purchases and devices.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Google Cloud includes infrastructure and platform services, collaboration tools, and other services for enterprise customers.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Google Cloud generates revenues primarily from consumption-based fees and subscriptions received for Google Cloud Platform services, Google Workspace communication and collaboration tools, and other enterprise services.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Other Bets is a combination of multiple operating segments that are not individually material. Revenues from Other Bets are generated primarily from the sale of healthcare-related services and internet services.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Revenues, certain costs, such as costs associated with content and traffic acquisition, certain engineering activities, and devices, as well as certain operating expenses are directly attributable to our segments.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Due to the integrated nature of Alphabet, other costs and expenses, such as technical infrastructure and office facilities, are managed centrally at a consolidated level.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: These costs, including the associated depreciation and impairment, are allocated to operating segments as a service cost generally based on usage, headcount, or revenue.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Reflecting DeepMind's increasing collaboration with Google Services, Google Cloud, and Other Bets, beginning in the first quarter of 2023 DeepMind is reported as part of Alphabet-level activities instead of within Other Bets.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Additionally, beginning in the first quarter of 2023, we updated and simplified our cost allocation methodologies to provide our business leaders with increased transparency for decision-making.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Prior periods have been recast to conform to the current presentation.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: As announced on April 20, 2023, we brought together part of Google Research (the Brain team) and DeepMind to significantly accelerate our progress in artificial intelligence (AI).

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The group, called Google DeepMind, is reported within Alphabet-level activities prospectively beginning in the second quarter of 2023.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Previously, the Brain team was included within Google Services.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Certain costs are not allocated to our segments because they represent Alphabet-level activities.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: These costs primarily include AI-focused shared R&D activities, including development costs of our general AI models; corporate initiatives such as our philanthropic activities; corporate shared costs such as certain finance, human resource, and legal costs, including certain fines and settlements.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Charges associated with reductions in our workforce and office space during 2023 were not allocated to our segments.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Additionally, hedging gains (losses) related to revenue are not allocated to our segments.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our operating segments are not evaluated using asset information.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Item 9ACONTROLS AND PROCEDURES Evaluation of Disclosure Controls and Procedures Our management, with the participation of our chief executive officer and chief financial officer, evaluated the effectiveness of our disclosure controls and procedures pursuant to Rule 13a-15 under the Exchange Act, as of the end of the period covered by this Annual Report on Form 10-K.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Based on this evaluation, our chief executive officer and chief financial officer concluded that, as of December 31, 2023, our disclosure controls and procedures are designed at a reasonable assurance level and are effective to provide reasonable assurance that information we are required to disclose in reports that we file or submit under the Exchange Act is recorded, processed, summarized, and reported within the time periods specified in the SEC's rules and forms, and that such information is accumulated and communicated to our management, including our chief executive officer and chief financial officer, as appropriate, to allow timely decisions regarding required disclosure.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Changes in Internal Control over Financial Reporting There have been no changes in our internal control over financial reporting that occurred during the quarter ended December 31, 2023 that have materially affected, or are reasonably likely to materially affect, our internal control over financial reporting.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Management's Report on Internal Control over Financial Reporting Our management is responsible for establishing and maintaining adequate internal control over financial reporting, as defined in Rule 13a-15(f) of the Exchange Act.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our management conducted an evaluation of the effectiveness of our internal control over financial reporting based on the framework in Internal Control-Integrated Framework issued by the Committee of Sponsoring Organizations of the Treadway Commission (2013 framework).

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Based on this evaluation, management concluded that our internal control over financial reporting was effective as of December 31, 2023.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Management reviewed the results of its assessment with our Audit and Compliance Committee.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The effectiveness of our internal control over financial reporting as of December 31, 2023 has been audited by Ernst & Young LLP, an independent registered public accounting firm, as stated in its report which is included in Item 8 of this Annual Report on Form 10-K.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Limitations on Effectiveness of Controls and Procedures In designing and evaluating the disclosure controls and procedures, management recognizes that any controls and procedures, no matter how well designed and operated, can provide only reasonable assurance of achieving the desired control objectives.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: In addition, the design of disclosure controls and procedures must reflect the fact that there are resource constraints and that management is required to apply its judgment in evaluating the benefits of possible controls and procedures relative to their costs.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Alphabet Inc.

sentence: Item 9BOTHER INFORMATION 10b5-1 Trading Plans During the fiscal quarter ended December 31, 2023, the following Section 16 officer and directors adopted, modified or terminated a "Rule 10b5-1 trading arrangement" (as defined in Item 408 of Regulation S-K of the Exchange Act):

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: John Hennessy, Chair of the Board of Directors, through the John L. Hennessy & Andrea J. Hennessy Revocable Trust, adopted a new trading plan on November 1, 2023 (with the first trade under the new plan scheduled for February 12, 2024).

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The trading plan will be effective until March 12, 2025 to sell 6,664 shares of Class C Capital Stock and 11,336 shares of Class A Common Stock.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Ann Mather, former member of the Board of Directors, terminated her trading plan on October 30, 2023, effective with her resignation from the Board of Directors.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The trading plan previously permitted the sale of 12,580 shares of Class C Capital Stock and would have been effective until June 2, 2024.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Ruth M. Porat, President and Chief Investment Officer; Chief Financial Officer, adopted a new trading plan on November 30, 2023 (with the first trade under the new plan scheduled for March 8, 2024).

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The trading plan will be effective until March 8, 2025 to sell all of the (net) shares of up to 82,900 (gross) Class C Capital Stock issued upon the vesting of her Alphabet 2021 Performance Stock Units, as adjusted based on performance (net shares are net of tax withholding).

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: There were no "non-Rule 10b5-1 trading arrangements" (as defined in Item 408 of Regulation S-K of the Exchange Act) adopted, modified or terminated during the fiscal quarter ended December 31, 2023 by our directors and Section 16 officers.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Each of the Rule 10b5-1 trading arrangements are in accordance with our Policy Against Insider Trading and actual sale transactions made pursuant to such trading arrangements will be disclosed publicly in Section 16 filings with the SEC in accordance with applicable securities laws, rules and regulations.
